<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-06T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-06T16:00:00-05:00" n="391" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d391">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/2470</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BRW1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-06T16:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">November 6, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2356. Your 4765, October 12.<note n="1" xml:id="d391fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_356">p.
                                    356</ref>.</note> The President wishes you to make in his behalf
                                a very courteous acknowledgment of message from Luxemburg, with
                                statement to effect that you have been asked by him to say that he
                                will have every disposition to regard the interests of Luxemburg in
                                the most friendly way.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>